Diag (in Support)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	Diag is a simple diagnosis program to get some info about your
	system. To use diag, you need an EMPTY disk.
	  
	First you're asked whether diag may save the results in a file
	in the ram disk 't:diag.results'. This file can be printed out
	with 'copy t:diag.results prt:'
	Now some general infomartion is displayed (processor, ram, ...).
	The next step examines your disk drives. That's important when
	you  have problems with an hd drive which isn't recognized as
	an hd one. You are asked to insert a dd disk in all drives first.
	The result should be '0x0' (or 0xFFFFFFFF for a not connected
	drive). Then the procedure is repeated with hd disks. They should
	return 0xAAAAAAAA.
	The final test will be repeated X times (where X is the number of
	drives you have). For this you need the EMPTY disk. This part
	FORMATS and counts the track(length). The actual length per track
	is displayed. At the end the average and the lowest track length
	is displayed (they shouldn't differ too much).
	You may repeat this step for each drive or several times for one
	drive. HD disks are recognized automatically.
	In case you have problems with DSD please send me the results of
	this test. And please remember, that I have to pay postage, too.
  
	Please don't 'play' with diag. It doesn`t catch all possibilities
	of errors or misuse. This may cause a crash!
	
@EndNode
